column4: When this option is selected, addresses will be formatted according to the rules of their countries. Otherwise, the primary location formatting will be applied.
Select the system language from the list of the installed translations (see System → Localization → Languages).
Select the languages that can be used to translate email templates.
Locale selection affects the formatting of numbers, addresses, names, and dates.
If Format address per country option is disabled, or there is no country-specific formatting, the addresses will be formatted according to the rules of primary location.
Set the date when the first quarter of the year starts.
Select the temperature unit. This settings will be applied for the weather on the map.
Select the timezone of your location. All dates and times will be displayed in the specified timezone.
Select the wind speed unit. This settings will be applied for the weather on the map.
The relationships between the localization item and other localization items that treat the localization item as a parent localization.

Localization item stores locale-specific configuration: the language code of the locale's main language, a formatting code that is used for the locale, and a parent localization that is used by default whenever the translation for the main language is missing.
Code of the formatting style that should apply in the localized instance.
A human readable localization name that helps identify settings for a particular locale.
The relationships between the localization item and its parent localization.
The relationship between the localization item and its localizable label that is used to refer to the localization in the UI.
Localizedfallbackvalue stores relationships between the text values (content like name, description, etc.) and their translation data.
The value for the localization, selected language
The string value for the curent localization
The text value for the curent localization, can contain html tags
To send notifications to specific people, type their email addresses separated by semicolons (;). Leave this field empty to disable error logs notification.
